SQL Sales & Customer Analytics Project
Project Overview

Designed and executed a comprehensive SQL-based sales and customer analysis project using transactional e-commerce data. The project involved writing basic, intermediate, and advanced SQL queries to analyze customer demographics, sales performance, revenue contribution, and customer retention behavior.

Key Responsibilities & Analysis Performed
Basic SQL Analysis

Extracted unique customer cities to understand geographic distribution.

Counted orders placed in a specific year (2017) for time-based analysis.

Calculated total sales by product category to identify top revenue drivers.

Computed the percentage of installment-based payments to analyze customer payment behavior.

Analyzed customer distribution by state to support regional market insights.

Intermediate SQL Analysis

Calculated monthly order volume for 2018 to identify seasonal trends.

Determined the average number of products per order, grouped by customer city.

Calculated the percentage contribution of each category to total revenue.

Analyzed the relationship between product price and purchase frequency.

Computed seller-wise total revenue and ranked sellers using window functions.

Advanced SQL Analysis

Calculated moving averages of order values for each customer to track spending behavior over time.

Generated cumulative monthly sales for each year to analyze growth patterns.

Calculated year-over-year (YoY) sales growth rates to measure business performance.

Measured customer retention rate, identifying customers who made repeat purchases within 6 months.

Identified top 3 highest-spending customers per year using ranking functions.

SQL Concepts & Techniques Used

JOINs (INNER, LEFT)

GROUP BY, HAVING

Aggregate functions (SUM, AVG, COUNT)

Date functions

Subqueries & CTEs

Window functions (RANK, DENSE_RANK, ROW_NUMBER)

Moving averages

Cumulative sums

Percentage calculations

Customer retention logic
Business Insights Delivered

Identified high-performing product categories and sellers.

Discovered seasonal order trends and yearly growth patterns.

Highlighted repeat customer behavior and retention rates.

Provided data-driven insights to support pricing, seller performance, and customer engagement strategies.
